asy yet notwithstanding all time bestowed notwithstanding mutual good inclinations his plan teaching excellent much labor made little progress very singular clear conception never learn much masters except father m lambercier little know besides learned alone seen hereafter spirit impatient every species constraint cannot submit law moment even fear learning prevents being attentive dread wearying those who teach makes feign understand thus proceed faster comprehend conclusion learn nothing understanding must take its own time cannot submit another time ordination being arrived m gatier returned his province deacon leaving gratitude attachment sorrow his loss vows made no more answered those offered myself some years after learned being vicar parish young girl child being only one though possessed very tender heart whom ever love dreadful scandal diocese severely governed where priests being good regulation ought never children except married women having infringed politic law put prison defamed driven his benefice know whether ever after his power reestablish his affairs remembrance his misfortunes which deeply engraven heart struck when wrote emilius uniting m gatier m gaime formed these two worthy priests character savoyard vicar flatter myself imitation dishonored originals while seminary m d aubonne obliged quit annecy moultou being displeased made love his wife which acting like dog manger though madam moultou extremely amiable lived very ill treating such brutality separation talked moultou repeated oppressions length procured dismissal his employment disagreeable man mole blacker nor owl more knavish said provincials revenge themselves enemies songs m d aubonne revenged himself his comedy which sent madam de warens who showed pleased immediately conceived idea writing one try whether silly author pronounced project executed till went chambery where wrote lover himself thus when said preface piece written eighteen cut off few years nearly time event happened 