ens gave some respite chimeras finding happiness real objects less inclined seek nonentities only found also means near agreeable situation having sent word procured one suit which should obliged quit exhausted all conjectures guessing what occupation must possessed art divination hit right money sufficient make journey agreeable mademoiselle du chatelet persuaded hire horse consent certainly right doing should lost pleasure last pedestrian expedition ever made cannot give name those excursions frequently taken own neighborhood while lived motiers very singular imagination never rises high when situation least agreeable cheerful when everything smiles around am least amused heart cannot confine itself realities cannot embellish must create real objects strike really imagination only decorate ideal ones if paint spring must winter if describe beautiful landscape must while surrounded walls said hundred times confined bastille draw most enchanting picture liberty departure lyons saw nothing agreeable future content now reason enjoyed great discontent been leaving paris notwithstanding during journey any those delightful reveries enjoyed mind serene all drew near excellent friend going see heart overflowing tenderness enjoying advance without intoxication pleasure living near always expected if nothing new happened meantime anxious employment madam de warens procured if alone been material ideas calm peaceable ravishing celestial every object struck sight its natural form observed surrounding landscape remarked trees houses springs deliberated cross roads fearful losing myself yet word no longer empyrean precisely where found myself sometimes perhaps end journey never farther am recounting travels making loath arrive conclusion heart beat joy approached dear madam de warens went no faster account love walk ease stop leisure strolling life necessary travelling foot fine country fine weather having agreeable object terminate journey manner living all others most suited t