es rehearsed first magazine afterwards great theatre audience very numerous great rehearsal several parts composition highly applauded however during rehearsal very ill conducted rebel felt piece received before appear great alterations necessary therefore withdrew without saying word exposing myself refusal plainly perceived several indications work been perfect succeeded m de francueil promised get rehearsed should received exactly kept his word thought perceived occasion well many others neither madam dupin nor himself willing should acquire certain reputation world lest after publication books should supposed grafted talents upon mine yet madam dupin always supposed those very moderate never employed except write what dictated researches pure erudition reproach respect been unjust last failure success completed discouragement abandoned every prospect fame advancement without further troubling head real imaginary talents which little success dedicated whole time cares procure myself theresa subsistence manner most pleasing those whom should agreeable provide therefore entirely attached myself madam dupin m de francueil place very opulent situation eight nine hundred livres which first two years scarcely enough provide primary wants being obliged live neighborhood dear part town furnished lodging having pay another lodging extremity paris very top rue saint jacques which let weather went almost every evening supper soon got track new occupations conceived taste attached myself study chemistry attended several courses m de francueil m rouelle s began scribble paper upon science which scarcely possessed elements 1717 went pass autumn tourraine castle chenonceaux royal mansion upon cher built henry diana poitiers whom ciphers still seen which now possession m dupin farmer general amused ourselves very agreeably beautiful place lived very well became fat there monk music favorite relaxation composed several trios full harmony which may perhaps speak supplement if ever