is whom formed better opinion afterwards m perdriau country pastor now professor belles lettres whose mild agreeable society ever make regret loss although since thought proper detach himself m jalabert time professor natural philosophy since become counsellor syndic whom read discourse upon inequality dedication which seemed delighted professor lullin whom maintained correspondence until his death who gave commission purchase books library professor vernet who like most other people turned his back upon after given proofs attachment confidence which ought been sensible if theologian affected anything chappins clerk successor gauffecourt whom wished supplant who soon afterwards himself supplanted marcet de mezieres old friend father s who also shown himself mine after having well deserved his country became dramatic author pretending council two hundred changed his principles before died became ridiculous whom expected most m moultou very promising young man his talents his brilliant imagination whom always loved although his conduct respect frequently equivocal withstanding his being connected most cruel enemies whom cannot look upon destined become defender memory avenger his friend midst these dissipations neither lost taste solitary excursions nor habit frequently made long ones upon banks lake during which mind accustomed reflection remain idle digested plan already formed political institutions which shall shortly speak meditated history valais plan tragedy prose subject which nothing less lucretia deprive hope succeeding although dared again exhibit unfortunate heroine when no longer suffered upon any french stage time tried abilities tacitus translated first books his history which found amongst papers after residence four months geneva returned month october paris avoided passing through lyons might again travel gauffecourt arrangement made require being geneva until spring following returned during winter habits occupations principal latter examining proof