ble daily james some his servants already clapped prison fort william strong suspicion complicity seemed noised all sides alan breck fired shot there bill issued both one hundred pounds reward all bad little note bouman carried us mrs stewart miserable sadness besought alan let himself captured assuring if fell hands troops both james no better dead men money sent all beg borrow prayed heaven doing lastly said enclosed us one bills which described looked upon great curiosity little fear partly man may look mirror partly might look barrel enemy s gun judge if truly aimed alan advertised small pock marked active man thirty five thereby dressed feathered hat french side coat blue silver buttons lace great deal tarnished red waistcoat breeches black shag tall strong lad eighteen wearing old blue coat very ragged old highland bonnet long homespun waistcoat blue breeches his legs bare low country shoes wanting toes speaks like lowlander no beard alan well enough pleased see his finery fully remembered set only when came word tarnish looked upon his lace like one little mortified myself thought cut miserable figure bill yet well enough pleased too since changed these rags description ceased danger become source safety alan said should change clothes na troth said alan nae others fine sight if went back france bonnet put second reflection mind if separate alan his tell tale clothes should safe against arrest might go openly business nor all suppose arrested when alone there little against suppose taken company reputed murderer case begin grave generosity s sake dare speak mind upon head thought none less thought all more too when bouman brought green purse four guineas gold best part another small change true more alan less five guineas get far france less two beyond queensferry taking things proportion alan s society only peril life burden purse there no thought sort honest head companion believed serving helping protecting what hold peace chafe take chance s little enough